                                         CAPE TOWN - Parliament's inquiry into Eskom is expected to continue on Tuesday. MPs will hear from the Eskom board and its suspended CFO Anoj Singh, who is accused of financial misconduct and faces disciplinary charges. The inquiry is investigating widespread corruption involving Gupta-aligned companies and executives at the state-owned power utility. WATCH LIVE: Eskom board appears before Parliament over state capture 